# Bu dosyayı kopyalayıp .env olarak kaydedin; jar yalnızca .env okur (.env.example otomatik yüklenmez).
# copy .env.example .env   (PowerShell: Copy-Item .env.example .env)

# Topla internal API (no trailing slash on base URL)
TOPLA_API_BASE_URL=https://www.topla.online
TOPLA_IMPORT_API_KEY=your-secret-import-key

# Logical bot identity — must match a key in deal-radar TOPLA_IMPORT_ACTOR_MAP (string only, not UUID)
TOPLA_ACTOR_KEY=topla_trendyol_bot

# Comma-separated scrapers: amazon, trendyol (default: amazon)
INGESTION_SOURCES=amazon

# Optional: fixed category for every imported deal (e.g. match a Topla category URL/slug you use)
# DEAL_CATEGORY=Elektronik

# When true, import sends metadata JSON (deal-radar may append it under [import] in description). Default: false
# TOPLA_IMPORT_SEND_METADATA=false

# Amazon mode: urls = AMAZON_URLS / AMAZON_START_URL (explicit product pages)
#              hub = open AMAZON_DEALS_HUB_URL, pick discounted links, scrape up to AMAZON_DEALS_TARGET_COUNT
AMAZON_MODE=urls
# AMAZON_MODE=hub
# AMAZON_DEALS_HUB_URL=https://www.amazon.com.tr/deals
# AMAZON_DEALS_TARGET_COUNT=3
# AMAZON_DEALS_RANDOM_SEED=42

# Single Amazon page (urls mode; used if AMAZON_URLS is unset)
AMAZON_START_URL=https://www.amazon.com.tr/
# Multiple product URLs → one deal per URL in one run (urls mode)
# AMAZON_URLS=https://www.amazon.com.tr/dp/PRODUCT1,https://www.amazon.com.tr/dp/PRODUCT2

# Browser
HEADLESS=true
BROWSER=chrome

# Selenium timeouts (ms)
PAGE_LOAD_TIMEOUT_MS=30000
IMPLICIT_WAIT_MS=5000

# API client
API_RETRY_COUNT=3
API_RETRY_DELAY_MS=1000
API_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_MS=10000
API_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS=30000
